  @startuml PY-001 Redesign — Theme System Sequence

  title dragon.py Theme System — Initialisation & Token Application

  actor Learner
  participant "Browser" as Browser
  participant "ThemeProvider\n(React component)" as TP
  participant "localStorage\n(dragonpy-theme)" as LS
  participant "/styles/themes/\ndragon.ts | light.ts" as Tokens
  participant "document.documentElement\n(:root)" as Root
  participant "LessonPage\ncomponents" as Page

  == App boot ==

  Learner -> Browser : opens any page
  Browser -> TP : mount ThemeProvider
  TP -> LS : read 'dragonpy-theme'
  alt key exists
    LS --> TP : 'dark' | 'light'
  else no key stored
    TP -> TP : default to 'dark'
  end

  TP -> Tokens : import theme object\n(dragon.ts or light.ts)
  Tokens --> TP : { '--bg-base': '#0f1117', ... }

  TP -> Root : setProperty() each token\ne.g. --bg-base, --accent-primary, etc.
  Root --> Page : CSS custom properties\navailable to all components

  == Render ==

  Page -> Page : render TitleBar, SkillBar,\nLessonPanel, CodePanel
  Page -> Page : every colour references\nvar(--token-name) only —\nno hardcoded hex in components

  Browser --> Learner : styled lesson page displayed

  == Future theme toggle (no UI required now) ==

  note over TP, LS
    When a toggle is added later:
    1. user clicks toggle
    2. ThemeProvider swaps token set
    3. writes new name to localStorage
    4. re-applies all tokens to :root
    No component refactoring needed.
  end note

  @enduml
